Management: Oral ciprofloxacin should not be taken with dairy products or calcium-fortified foods alone, but may be taken with meals that contain these products.  When taken alone, dairy products or calcium-fortified foods should be ingested at least 2 hours before or after ciprofloxacin administration.  When ciprofloxacin tablets are administered to patients receiving continuous enteral nutrition, some experts recommend that the tube feeding should be interrupted for at least 1 hour before and 2 hours after the dose of ciprofloxacin is given.  Patients should be monitored for altered antimicrobial efficacy and switched to intravenous ciprofloxacin if necessary.  If no enteral route besides a jejunostomy tube is available, it is also recommended to switch to intravenous ciprofloxacin.  According to the manufacturer, ciprofloxacin oral suspension should not be administered via nasogastric or feeding tubes due to its physical characteristics.', 'DDInter', 0, NULL);
